To build the PolarFire SOC image using this buildroot external tree:

1. git clone https://github.com/buildroot/buildroot.git -b 2021.02
2. git clone https://bitbucket.microchip.com/scm/~c41329/buildroot-pf-soc-external.git
3. cd buildroot-pf-soc-external
4. git checkout v2021.04
5. make O=$PWD $BR2_EXTERNAL=$PWD -C ../buildroot icicle_defconfig
6. make

When building completes program the image to the icicle kit:

1. run usbdmsc on the HSS console and determine the enumerated disk
   (i.e sda, sdb, etc.).  Make sure to unmount the disk if it automounts

2. dd if=images/sdcard.img of=/dev/sdN

3. Reboot the icicle kit or CTRL-C on the HSS console and type boot
